Not Going Out is a British television sitcom that has aired on BBC One since 2006. Starring Lee Mack, Megan Dodds, Tim Vine, Sally Bretton, Miranda Hart and Katy Wix, it was initially written by Mack, Andrew Collins, Paul Kerensa, Simon Evans and Peter Tilbury, but now features contributions from other writers. The first series was directed by Hardcastle and Wood, the second series exclusively by Hardcastle, and the third, fourth, fifth and sixth series exclusively by Wood
